title: Complete quadrilateral and a polar triangle
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$A,B,C,D$$ be points on a non-degenerate [[conic|Projective conic]]. Then the points

$$
AB\cap CD,\quad AC\cap BD,\quad AD\cap BC
$$

form a //polar triangle//, i.e. each of the points is the [[pole|Pole-polar relationship]] of the line through the other two.